for_developers/README.md
     1→# For developers
     3→While `mdbook` is mainly used as a command line tool, you can also import the
     4→underlying libraries directly and use those to manage a book. It also has a fairly
     5→flexible plugin mechanism, allowing you to create your own custom tooling and
     6→consumers (often referred to as *backends*) if you need to do some analysis of
     7→the book or render it in a different format.
     8→
     9→The *For Developers* chapters are here to show you the more advanced usage of
    10→`mdbook`.
    11→
    12→The two main ways a developer can hook into the book's build process is via,
    13→
    14→- [Preprocessors](preprocessors.md)
    15→- [Alternative Backends](backends.md)
    16→
    17→## The build process
    19→The process of rendering a book project goes through several steps.
    20→
    21→1. Load the book
    22→    - Parse the `book.toml`, falling back to the default `Config` if it doesn't
    23→       exist
    24→    - Load the book chapters into memory
    25→    - Discover which preprocessors/backends should be used
    26→2. For each backend:
    27→   1. Run all the preprocessors.
    28→   2. Call the backend to render the processed result.
    29→
    30→## Using `mdbook` as a library
    32→The `mdbook` binary is just a wrapper around the underlying mdBook crates,
    33→exposing their functionality as a command-line program. If you want to
    34→programmatically drive mdBook, you can use the [`mdbook-driver`] crate.
    35→This can be used to add your own functionality or tweak the build process.
    36→
    37→The easiest way to find out how to use the `mdbook-driver` crate is by looking at the
    38→[API Docs]. The top level documentation explains how one would use the
    39→[`MDBook`] type to load and build a book, while the [config] module gives a good
    40→explanation on the configuration system.
    41→
    42→[`MDBook`]: https://docs.rs/mdbook-driver/latest/mdbook_driver/struct.MDBook.html
    43→[API Docs]: https://docs.rs/mdbook-driver/latest/mdbook_driver/
    44→[config]: https://docs.rs/mdbook-driver/latest/mdbook_driver/config/index.html
